{
  "title": "\"My Girlfriends Could Fill A Yanu-Yanu Bus\"",
  "abstract": "In this paper, I investigate the ways that young men in rural southern Malawi talk about HIV and their own perceptions of risk. I relate these findings first to evolving gender relations in Malawi during the AIDS epidemic, and second to HIV prevention",
